data-triple-N3.o: "The Wales national rugby union team (Welsh: Tim rygbi'r undeb cenedlaethol Cymru) represent Wales in international rugby union tournaments. They compete annually in the Six Nations Championship with England, France, Ireland, Italy and Scotland. Wales have won the Six Nations and its predecessors 26 times outright, joint-first with England. Wales' most recent championship win came in 2013. They also compete in the Rugby World Cup every four years."@en
